PEOPLE living with dementia are being invited to a sing-along featuring hits from across the years.The 'Singing for the Brain ' group says joining in builds on preserved memory.The songsters will meet from 1-3pm on Friday May 8 at Newton Mearns Church, Ayr Road and anyone from across East Renfrewshire who would benefit is welcome to take part.If you know someone who would like to take part or for more info please call David Murray or Alan Stevenson on 0141 800 7070.The group is running in partnership with East Ren CHCP's Kirkton Service and The Richmond Fellowship.The Richmond Fellowship support individuals with a diagnosis of dementia throughout East Renfrewshire while the Kirkton Service works together with older people to identify the things that are important to them and help them live a full happy life within their community.